Cameroon’s Average Cocoa Export Price Advanced 6.8% Last Week

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-08-08T10:39:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/cameroon-s-average-cocoa-export-price-advanced-6-8-last-week.html
The average price for cocoa exports
from Cameroon’s main port of Douala increased by 6.8 percent in
the week to Aug. 7, according to the country’s Cocoa and Coffee
Board.  The price rose 91 CFA Francs to 1,435 CFA francs ($3.14) a
kilogram (2.2 pounds), the board said today in a mobile phone
text message.  Total production up to June 30 since the season started in
August came up to 229,040 metric tons, the board said last
month. Annual production for 2009-2010 season was 198,000 tons,
it said in August.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde at 
 plukong@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
